Head (
Fig. 195 A-D
). Head rounded with pubescence long and dense. Proximal three antennal flagellomeres longer than wide (0.15:0.07, 0.16:0.07, 0.16:0.070), distal antennal flagellomere longer than penultimate (0.11:0.04, 0.08:0.04), antenna longer than body (2.46, 2.22); antennal scrobes-frons shallow. Face convex with dense fine punctations, interspaces smooth and longitudinal median carina present. Frons smooth. Temple wide, punctate and interspaces clearly smooth. Inner margin of eyes diverging slightly at antennal sockets; in lateral view, eye anteriorly convex and posteriorly straight. POL shorter than OOL (0.95, 0.11). Malar suture present. Median area between lateral ocelli slightly depressed. Vertex laterally pointed or nearly so and dorsally wide.

